Target: OntoZoning is an ontology developed to represent relationships between zoning types, land uses and programmes (more specific land uses).

Comment: Broad land use categories that are allowed in a specific zoning type in Singapore. Land uses may have further regulations attached, e.g. maximum use quantums. For example, a land use might be ‘Commercial or Hotel Use in Commercial Zone’. This land use is broad in the sense that a commercial use encompasses more specific uses like ‘restaurant’, ‘bar’ and ‘bookstore.’ This land use is necessary to describe at this level of detail because in Singapore, a minimum use quantum of 60% applies to it, meaning that at least 60% of the GFA of a plot zoned as Commercial must be devoted to a mix of different commercial or hotel uses which may include, for example, 'restaurant', 'bar', and 'bookstore'.
Label: Land Use

Comment: The zoning type is a legally-binding description of the permittable ‘uses’ and ‘developments’ that are or may not be allowed to be constructed within a specific zone or area delineated. Zoning types are defined by a governing authority and are usually tailored to specific contexts.
Label: Zoning Type

Comment: These are areas used or intended to be used for agricultural purposes and includes plant nursery.
Label: Agriculture

Comment: These are areas used or intended to be used for coastal recreational purposes for the enjoyment of the general public.
Label: Beach Area

Comment: A zoning type tailored to URA in Singapore. These are areas used or intended to be used mainly for clean industry, light industry, public utilities, and telecommunication uses and other public installations for which the relevant authority does not impose a nuisance buffer greater than 50m. General industrial uses that are able to meet the nuisance buffer requirements imposed by the relevant authority for general industries may be allowed in the B1 zones, subject to evaluation by the relevant authority and the competent authority.
Label: Business 1

Comment: These are areas used or intended to be used mainly for uses permissible under B1 zone and White zone as a mixed use development.
Label: Business 1 White

Comment: A zoning type tailored to URA in Singapore. There are areas used or intended to be used for clean industry, light industry, general industry, warehouse, public utilities and telecommunication uses and other public installations. Special industries such as manufacture of industrial machinery, shipbuilding and repairing, may be allowed in selected areas subject to evaluation by the relevant authority and the competent authority.
Label: Business 2

Comment: These are areas used or intended to be used mainly for uses permissible under B2 zone and White zone as a mixed use development.
Label: Business 2 White

Comment: These are areas used or intended to be used for business park operations.
Label: Business Park

Comment: These are areas used or intended to be used mainly for business park operations and other uses permissible under White zone as a mixed use development.
Label: Business Park White

Comment: These are areas used or intended to be used for burial grounds, crematoria and columbaria.
Label: Cemetery Zone

Comment: These are areas used or intended to be used mainly for civic, community or cultural facilities or other similar purposes.
Label: Civic And Community Institution Zone

Comment: These are areas used or intended to be used mainly for commercial development.
Label: Commercial

Comment: These are areas used or intended to be used mainly for mixed commercial and residential development.
Label: Commercial And Residential

Comment: These are areas used or intended to be used mainly for commercial purpose, community institution facilities or other similar purposes.
Label: Commercial Or Institution

Comment: These are areas used or intended to be used mainly for educational purposes including tertiary education.
Label: Educational Institution

Comment: These are areas used or intended to be used mainly for medical services.
Label: Health And Medical Care

Comment: These are areas used or intended to be used mainly for hotel development
Label: Hotel Zone

Comment: These are areas used or intended to be used as open space.
Label: Open Space

Comment: These are areas used or intended to be used mainly for parks or gardens for the enjoyment of the general public and includes pedestrian linkages.
Label: Park

Comment: These are areas used or intended to be used mainly for religious buildings.
Label: Place Of Worship

Comment: These are areas used or intended to be used for airport/ airfield or dock/port purposes.
Label: Port Or Airport

Comment: These are areas used or intended to be used mainly for Rapid Transit purposes.
Label: Rapid Transit

Comment: These are areas the specific use of which has yet to be determined. Interim uses that are compatible with the uses in the locality may be allowed subject to evaluation by the competent authority.
Label: Reserve Site

Comment: These are areas used or intended to be used mainly for residential development.
Label: Residential

Comment: These are areas used or intended to be used mainly for residential purpose, community institution facilities or other similar purposes.
Label: Residential Or Institution

Comment: These are areas used or intended to be used mainly for residential development with commercial use at the first storey only.
Label: Residential With Commercial At First Storey

Comment: These are areas used or intended to be used for existing and proposed roads.
Label: Road

Comment: These are areas used or intended to be used for special purposes.
Label: Special Use Zone

Comment: These are areas used or intended to be used mainly for sports and recreational purposes.
Label: Sports And Recreation

Comment: These are areas used or intended to be used mainly for the parking of vehicles and transport facilities including garages and at-grade structure of underground road tunnel and rapid transit system.
Label: Transport Facilities

Comment: These are areas used or intended to be used mainly for public utilities and telecommunication infrastructure, including water works, sewage disposal works and other public installations such as electrical substations.
Label: Utility

Comment: These are areas used or intended to be used for drainage purposes and water areas such as reservoirs, ponds, rivers and other water channels.
Label: Waterbody

Comment: A zoning type tailored to URA in Singapore. These are areas used or intended to be used mainly for commercial, hotel, residential, sports & recreational and other compatible uses, or a combination of two or more such uses as a mixed development.
Label: White

Comment: More specific land uses that are allowed in one or more broader land use categories. For example, ‘restaurant’, ‘bar’ and ‘bookstore’ are programmes. No use quantums are attached to programmes.
Label: Programme

Comment: The list of programmes in this ontology is currently derived from three distinctive sources. However, the list of programmes in this ontology may be extended through other sources. Hence, to know where from every programme is coming from, their source needs to be explicitly defined.
Label: Source

Comment: A ratio between the predominant allowed uses and the ancillary allowed uses by the zoning type expressed in percentage. For instance, Business 2 zoning type allows at least 60% of the floor area to be dedicated for industrial purpose uses and the remaining 40% may be dedicated for ancillary uses such as Showroom, Industrial Canteen, Ancillary Office, etc.
Label: Use Quantum
